{"pageTitle":"Spring Data JDBC - CSS","title":"Spring Data JDBC","content":"<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Spring Data JDBC, part of the larger Spring Data family, makes it easy to implement JDBC based repositories. This module deals with enhanced support for JDBC based data access layers. It makes it easier to build Spring powered applications that use data access technologies.</p><h2 id=\"features\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 1.1428em 0px 0.5714em; padding: 1rem 0px; font-size: 22px; font-weight: 500; font-family: Metropolis, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.125; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; position: relative;\">Features</h2><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 1em 0px 0px 2em; padding: 0px; list-style: outside disc; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><a href=\"https://spring.io/blog/2022/01/20/spring-data-jdbc-how-can-i-do-a-partial-update-of-an-aggregate-root\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(8, 109, 195); cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none;\">Based on the aggregate abstraction</a></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.25em 0px 0px; padding: 0px;\">Annotation based entity mapping</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.25em 0px 0px; padding: 0px;\">Immutable entities</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.25em 0px 0px; padding: 0px;\">Query derivation</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.25em 0px 0px; padding: 0px;\">Custom queries via<span>&nbsp;</span><code style=\"box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-font-smoothing: auto; font-family: Monaco, monospace; color: rgb(0, 0, 153); font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 400; padding: 2px 6px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border: 1px solid rgb(225, 225, 232); white-space: nowrap;\">@Query</code><span>&nbsp;</span>annotations</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.25em 0px 0px; padding: 0px;\">MyBatis integration</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.25em 0px 0px; padding: 0px;\">Lifecycle callbacks</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.25em 0px 0px; padding: 0px;\">Auditing</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.25em 0px 0px; padding: 0px;\">modified_undeploy</li></ul>"}